claim.claim-text:
1. A semiconductor device comprising: 
a semiconductor film comprising crystalline silicon formed on an insulating surface; 
a channel region formed in the semiconductor film; 
a gate insulating film adjacent to the semiconductor film; and 
a gate electrode adjacent to the channel region with the gate insulating film interposed therebetween, 
wherein the semiconductor film has a {110} orientation and a concentration of C (carbon), N (nitrogen), and S (sulfur) in the semiconductor film is less than 5×1018 atoms/cm3, and a concentration of O (oxygen) in the semiconductor film is less than 1.5×1019 atoms/cm3.

5. A semiconductor device comprising: 
a semiconductor film comprising crystalline silicon formed on an insulating surface; 
a channel region formed in the semiconductor film; 
a gate insulating film adjacent to the semiconductor film; and 
a gate electrode adjacent to the channel region with the gate insulating film interposed therebetween, 
wherein the semiconductor film has a {110} orientation and a concentration of C (carbon), N (nitrogen), and S (sulfur) in the semiconductor film is less than 5×1018 atoms/cm3, and a concentration of O (oxygen) in the semiconductor film is less than 1.5×1019 atoms/cm3, and a ratio of the {110} orientation is not smaller than 0.9.

9. A semiconductor device comprising: 
a crystalline semiconductor film formed on an insulating surface; 
a channel region formed in the semiconductor film; 
a gate insulating film adjacent to the semiconductor film; and 
a gate electrode adjacent to the channel region with the gate insulating film interposed therebetween, 
wherein the semiconductor film has a {110} orientation and a concentration of C (carbon), N (nitrogen), and S (sulfur) in the semiconductor film is less than 5×1018 atoms/cm3, and a concentration of O (oxygen) in the semiconductor film is less than 1.5×1019 atoms/cm3, and said crystalline semiconductor film comprises SiXGe1-x (0.9≦X≦0.99).

13. A semiconductor device comprising: 
a semiconductor film comprising a plurality of silicon crystals formed on an insulating surface, said plurality of silicon crystals extending approximately in one direction; 
a channel region formed in the semiconductor film; 
a gate insulating film adjacent to the semiconductor film; and 
a gate electrode adjacent to the channel region with the gate insulating film interposed therebetween, 
wherein the semiconductor film has a {110} orientation and a concentration of C (carbon), N (nitrogen), and S (sulfur) in the semiconductor film is less than 5×1018 atom s/cm3, and a concentration of O (oxygen) in the semiconductor film is less than 1.5×1019 atoms/cm3.
